<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="1740" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="9.[144,1103,1218,1345]" box="[144,276,1218,1242]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1740">
<heading box="[144,276,1218,1242]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="1740" reason="5">
<emphasis box="[144,276,1218,1242]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1740">Distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[144,1103,1218,1345]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1740">
Europe, Mediterranean basin/Cosmopolitan (
<bibRefCitation author="Cowie RH" box="[662,797,1257,1281]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1740" pagination="23 - 40" refId="ref9690" refString="Cowie RH. 2001. Can snails ever be effective and safe biocontrol agents? Int J Pest Manage. 47: 23 - 40." type="journal article" year="2001">Cowie 2001</bibRefCitation>
), invasive in Far East and South America (
<bibRefCitation author="Miquel SE &amp; Parent H &amp; Scarabino F" box="[329,535,1289,1313]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1740" pagination="26 - 75" refId="ref12262" refString="Miquel SE, Parent H, Scarabino F. 1995. Achatinoidea introducidos en la Argentina y el Uruguay (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Stylommatophorida). Neotropica. 41: 26 - 75." type="journal article" year="1995">Miquel et al. 1995</bibRefCitation>
). The first and only record for 
<collectingCountry box="[888,947,1289,1313]" name="Chile" pageId="9" pageNumber="1740">Chile</collectingCountry>
does not give precise data (
<bibRefCitation author="Rumi A &amp; Sanchez J &amp; Ferrando NS" box="[295,487,1321,1345]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1740" pagination="2985 - 2990" refId="ref13451" refString="Rumi A, Sanchez J, Ferrando NS. 2010. Theba pisana (Muller, 1774) (Gastropoda, Helicidae) and other alien land molluscs species in Argentina. Biol Invasions. 12: 2985 - 2990." type="journal article" year="2010">Rumi et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
